  "generated_text": "To find the total number of bolts of fiber the robe takes, we need to calculate the amount of blue and white fiber separately and then add them together.\n\n1.  **Identify the amount of blue fiber**:\n    The problem states that the robe takes 2 bolts of blue fiber.\n    $$ \\text{Blue bolts} = 2 $$\n\n2.  **Calculate the amount of white fiber**:\n    The problem states that the robe takes \"half that much white fiber\" (referring to the blue fiber).\n    $$ \\text{White bolts} = \\frac{1}{2} \\times 2 = 1 $$\n\n3.  **Calculate the total number of bolts**:\n    Add the blue and white bolts together.\n    $$ \\text{Total bolts} = \\text{Blue bolts} + \\text{White bolts} $$\n    $$ \\text{Total bolts} = 2 + 1 = 3 $$\n\nThe robe takes a total of 3 bolts.\n\n\\boxed{3}\n",
